com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.input
Interface IInputSource2Utils

All Known Implementing Classes:
InputSource2Utils
public interface IInputSource2Utils

For those projects that require full, static-free mocking capabilities, use this interface. Else, the concrete implementation InputSource2Utils or InputSource2Utils.INSTANCE will suffice.

Author:
Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
See Also:

inputSource - an input source reference
argName - argument name for inputSource, e.g., "strList" or "searchRegex"
Throws:
NullPointerException - if inputSource is null
IllegalArgumentException -

checkValid

void checkValid(Collection<? extends InputSource2> inputSourceCollection,
                String argName)
Tests if a Collection of InputSource2 is not empty and has valid elements (non-null, and each with exactly one byte- or character-stream).

Parameters:
inputSourceCollection - a collection of input sources reference
argName - argument name for inputSourceCollection, e.g., "strList" or "searchRegex"
Throws:
NullPointerException - if inputSourceCollection (or any element) is null
IllegalArgumentException - if number of elements in inputSourceCollection is zero
See Also:
checkValid(InputSource2, String)
